source .venv/bin/activate          # on Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python analysis.py
```

Or open `analysis.ipynb` in JupyterLab and run the cells top to bottom.

## Reproducibility scope

factorial's agent does not invent numbers — it calls the same
`process_improve.tool_spec.execute_tool_call` dispatch this script
uses. That means the **numeric outputs** of every tool (design
matrices, ANOVA tables, coefficients, p-values, VIF, aliasing,
efficiency, prediction-variance maps) will be identical across
machines running the same `process-improve` version.

Plot images are re-rendered locally, so pixel-level differences are
expected when fonts or renderer versions drift between the web UI
and your local environment. The underlying numeric content driving
those plots stays reproducible.

